Here flag would be not bool, but std::vector<bool>::reference, since for bool specialization of template vector

the operator [] returns a proxy object with conversion operator operator bool deﬁned.

When flags.push_back(true) modiﬁes the container, this pseudo-reference could end up dangling, referring to an

element that no longer exists.

It also makes the next situation possible:

